Brand story:
Innovator IBM begins the second century of its existence
If someone was looking for a word that would most accurately express IBM’s strategy, the closest approach would probably be “long term.”
For the general public, IBM is a symbol of the technological revolution, it is a company perceived as very modern, and yet a hundred years have passed since its founding.
The foundation of this long-termness was laid by the first CEO of the company, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
Already he had coined the slogan that many of the world’s problems could be easily solved if people were willing to think.
His slogan "Think!" became the imprint around which the life of the future giant will unfold (and also the name of an internal magazine that began to be published at IBM in 1935).
