Leaders were inspired by operations in other cities.
Massive exercises in case of behavior in crisis situations took place in the part of Randalls Island, which was a preparation for an event in Zuccotti Park.
Leaders have stepped up so-called riot-control training — counter-terrorism measures involving the rapid movement of large numbers of police officers — focusing on the Lower Manhattan district.
The last part of the training took place on Monday night, on the Manhattan side of the East River.
The orders to move to the park came literally “at the last minute,” said someone to whom the action was originally explained only as an “exercise.”
