In addition, a total recount of votes in all ballot boxes will be possible if there are indications that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the second-placed candidate is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever an explicit request from a party representative and/or coalition that proposed the second-placed candidate appears at the beginning of the session.
The total recount of votes will also be possible if, after proper counting, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the second-placed candidate is equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there will be an explicit request from a political party whose candidate ended in second place. In this case, the electoral packages for which partial recounts were made will be discarded.
