Europe invented democracy, it remains to think about European democracy
Democracy is a rare and fragile commodity.
The European continent should remember this, because despite having invented it in Athens two thousand years ago, it experienced the tragedy of world wars, totalitarian regimes, the Holocaust, the Gulags, but also Franco in Spain, Salazar in Portugal and colonels in Greece during the 20th century.
