The creation of a terrorist axis in Africa, which should lead from Mauritania via Nigeria to Somalia, is now a concern for all security specialists.
Now that al-Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb has surrounded Mali and the Al-Shabaab Somalis are operating in Kenya, Boko Haram is emerging as a new threat to the continent.
